<comment datatype='string'>Transcription of the genes &lt;i&gt;fimA&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;fimB&lt;/i&gt;, and &lt;i&gt;fimE&lt;/i&gt; appears to be indirectly repressed by the protein GadE under low pH. The proteins GadW and GadX and also CRP seem to regulate the three &lt;i&gt;fim&lt;/i&gt; genes, but it has not been determined if this regulation is direct [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/35316170&quot;&gt;Schwan22&lt;/a&gt;]. During stationary phase, RpoS causes a negative effect on transcription of the &lt;i&gt;fimA&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;fimB&lt;/i&gt; genes but not &lt;i&gt;fimE&lt;/i&gt; [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/35316170&quot;&gt;Schwan22&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
